text-transform: capitalize;
text-align: center;

Exercise: Define a new class in CSS with a bunch of attributes. Create a new paragraph tag <p>, 
and set its class attribute to the class you just created, e.g., <p class="my-fancy-class">.

Research Question: What happens if you give an element more than one CSS class?

